Production Deployment: Kubernetes (References Found)
1. Pod IP and Callback URL Mechanism
The system is designed for Kubernetes with support for multiple pod instances and callbacks.

From glide_rest_api.py:265-285:

python
def _enrich_meta_with_execution_context(self, meta: dict) -> dict:
    enriched_meta = meta.copy() if meta else {}
    
    # Rename podIp and fqsn to pod_ip and callback_url
    if "podIp" in enriched_meta:
        enriched_meta["pod_ip"] = enriched_meta.pop("podIp")
    if "fqsn" in enriched_meta:
        enriched_meta["callback_url"] = enriched_meta.pop("fqsn")
    
    # Extract from execution context if available
    if execution_context is not None:
        execution_context_meta: dict = execution_context.original_payload.get("meta", {})
        if "pod_ip" not in enriched_meta:
            enriched_meta["pod_ip"] = execution_context_meta.get("podIp", "")
        if "callback_url" not in enriched_meta:
            enriched_meta["callback_url"] = execution_context_meta.get("fqsn", "")
    
    return enriched_meta
Purpose:

podIp - IP address of the specific Kubernetes pod handling the request
fqsn (Fully Qualified Service Name) - Callback URL for async responses
Enables ServiceNow to call back to the specific pod that initiated the request
