Async Tool Execution & Callbacks
Why podIp and callback_url Matter
From the tool execution flow:

1. User request → Load balancer → Pod A (IP: 10.0.1.5)
    ↓
2. Pod A executes tool via ServiceNow
    meta: {
      "podIp": "10.0.1.5",
      "callback_url": "https://agent-orchestrator-pod-a.cluster.local:8050"
    }
    ↓
3. ServiceNow executes tool (async)
    ↓
4. ServiceNow calls back to specific pod:
    POST https://agent-orchestrator-pod-a.cluster.local:8050/callback
    ↓
5. Pod A receives callback with tool results
    ↓
6. Pod A continues execution with cached state
Without podIp/callback_url: Callback might go to wrong pod (no shared state)

